The variant CSS in the `<style>` tag won't match these hashed classes. This is the fundamental issue with live mode + CSS Modules.

However, I notice the section-header has `data-component` attributes or structural selectors I could use. Let me check the actual rendered HTML more carefully.

From the outerHTML:
- Section header div: `<div class="_root_1v939_6"><div class="_row_1v939_13"><span class="_label_1v939_19">THEMES</span></div><hr class="_rule_1v939_36"></div>`
- Theme list items: `<button class="_item_j5prl_15 _selected_j5prl_33">...`
- Group labels: `<div class="_groupLabel_j5prl_5">Default (4)</div>`

I can't target these with semantic class names in the variant CSS. I have a few options:

1. Use the hashed class names in the CSS (fragile but works for preview)
2. Use attribute selectors based on structure/text content
3. Use `!important` universal selectors scoped within the variant

Actually, the cleanest approach for live preview is to use `@scope` with the variant wrapper and target elements by their structure within the variant:

```css
@scope ([data-impeccable-variant="1"]) {
    /* Section header label — first span inside the first div inside .left */
    :scope .left > div:first-of-type span {
        font-size: 2.25rem !important;
    }
    /* etc */
}
```

But this is fragile too. Let me use the actual hashed class names. They won't change between page loads for this build.

